title: The-Laura-Ingraham-Show-Podcast May 16 2016
description:
Laura Ingraham Podcast May 16, 2016 MP3

Guest Host Betsy McCaughey welcomes: Dr. Sam Clovis "We're dealing with two candidates with relatively high negatives". Columnist John Fund on Trump Tax returns "a ticking time bomb for the GOP". CNBC commentator Larry Kulow on Trump tax plan "Nothing's been put on paper, the candidate, Mr Trump has not signed off on anything". Manhattan Institute scholar Heather McDonald on Police issues "officers are facing extraordinary hatred" 

Trump presidency would revive neutered Congress, restore power to the people
Charles Hurt - Washington Times
Unruly voters have elected an opportunistic showman as their presidential nominee. They were aided by infiltrators in the primary who were not even Republicans.


Trump vs. Clinton, Beyond the Cage Match
Karl Rove - Wall Street Journal
This presidential campaign is good at producing attention-grabbing train wrecks. Last week Hillary Clinton attacked Donald Trump as "a loose cannon." In turn, Mr. Trump called Mrs. Clinton "the total enabler" of her husband's affairs, and then he suggested that America repudiate some of its national 


The Federal Bullies Strike Again
The U.S. Department of Education will tell school districts Friday that federal law requires them to allow students to use restrooms and locker rooms "consistent with their gender identity," escalating the pressure from the Obama administration on the contentious public debate over transgender rights.


Sen. Sessions: Election offers a simple choice
Jeff Sessions - USA Today
For the first time in a long time, this November will give Americans a clear choice on perhaps the most important issue facing our country and our civilization: whether we remain a nation-state that serves its own people, or whether we slide irrevocably toward a soulless globalism that treats humans as interchangeable widgets in the world market.
